  "text": "Thirty-two singleton fetuses of time-mated Texel ewes were randomized by an independent researcher who was not involved in the animal experiments. Randomization resulted in four experimental groups: (1) sham umbilical cord occlusion, saline treatment (sham-SAL n = 8), [CITATION_1] sham umbilical cord occlusion, MAPC treatment (sham-MAPC; n = 8), (3) umbilical cord occlusion, saline treatment (HI-SAL; n = 8), and (4) umbilical cord occlusion, MAPC treatment (HI-MAPC; n = 8) (Fig. 1) . The investigator performing the (sham) umbilical cord occlusions was blinded to treatment allocation. Tissue sampling and the analyses of brain tissue and electrophysiological data were conducted in a blinded fashion.",
